.TH "MERGELOG\-RS" "1" "2026\-03\-15" ""
.SH mergelog\-rs
Merge and sort HTTP log files chronologically \(em Rust rewrite of \c
.UR https://ftp.iij.ad.jp/pub/pkgsrc/distfiles/mergelog-4.5.tar.gz
mergelog 4.5
.UE \c
\ by Bertrand Demiddelaer.
.SS Synopsis
.IP
.EX
mergelog\-rs [OPTIONS] <FILE>...
.EE
.SS Description
\f[CR]mergelog\-rs\f[R] reads multiple HTTP log files in \f[B]NCSA
Combined Log Format\f[R] and writes a single chronologically sorted
stream to stdout (or a file).
It is designed for consolidating logs from multiple servers behind a
round\-robin DNS.
.PP
All input files must be sorted chronologically within themselves (as
Apache and nginx produce them).
Timestamps are compared in UTC \(em timezone offsets in the log lines
are correctly handled.
.SS Log Format
The expected log line format is the NCSA Combined Log Format:
.IP
.EX
%h %l %u %t \(dq%r\(dq %>s %b \(dq%{Referer}i\(dq \(dq%{User\-agent}i\(dq
.EE
.PP
Example:
.IP
.EX
93.184.216.34 \- alice [15/Mar/2026:12:00:00 +0100] \(dqGET /index.html HTTP/1.1\(dq 200 4096 \(dqhttps://example.com/\(dq \(dqMozilla/5.0\(dq
.EE
.PP
The timestamp field \f[CR]%t\f[R] uses the format
\f[CR][DD/Mon/YYYY:HH:MM:SS ±HHMM]\f[R].
.PP
Lines whose timestamp cannot be parsed are sorted to the \f[B]end\f[R]
of the output (matching the behaviour of the original mergelog 4.5).
