.PP
mergelog\-rs is \f[B]2.26× faster\f[R] than the original, using a k\-way
heap merge (O(N log K)) instead of the original\(cqs second\-by\-second
iteration (O(timespan × K)).
.PP
The higher memory usage comes from 4 MiB read buffers per input file (7
× 4 MiB = 28 MiB).
This can be reduced by adjusting \f[CR]READER_BUF\f[R] in
\f[CR]src/reader.rs\f[R] if memory is constrained.
.SS Limitations
.IP \(bu 2
Input files must be individually sorted by timestamp (standard
Apache/nginx behaviour).
.IP \(bu 2
Only one file can be read from stdin at a time (\f[CR]\-\f[R]).
.IP \(bu 2
The \f[CR]\-\-format\f[R] flag is reserved for future formats; only
\f[CR]clf\f[R] is currently supported.
.IP \(bu 2
Open file descriptor limit applies (\f[CR]ulimit \-n\f[R]).
Increase with \f[CR]ulimit \-n 65536\f[R] if merging many files.
